cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.THEORY, cs.MS 

This paper compares a recently developed domain-theoretic model of OOP (NOOP) to other domain-theoretic models of OOP, which suggests that it falls under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the mathematical account for the relation between nominal and structural OO type systems, which could also place it under the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Theoretical Computer Science (cs.THEORY), and Mathematical Software (cs.MS) sub-categories.
